HP’s laptops have a strong reputation, and its ProBook x360 11 range extends their dominance into the education sector. The HP ProBook x360 11 Education Edition has everything you could ever need for your studies – whether you’re a high-school learner or tertiary education student. Get here to learn more about the ITMaster Education Initiative.
Click here to get in contact with ITMaster. We take a look at this functional laptop, below. The Education Edition of the HP ProBook x360 11 offers 8GB of RAM and 256GB of PCIe NVMe SSD storage. Alongside its powerful Intel Pentium processer and Intel UHD graphics, this will ensure your apps all load and run smoothly. These laptops also come with Windows 11 as standard, and boast a 48Wh Lithium-ion battery that will let you work for hours before needing to recharge. The ProBook x360 11 supports Wi-Fi 6, too, giving you the fastest Internet speeds and ensures you can stay connected at all times. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-581232" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ITMaster-PIc-1.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ITMaster-PIc-1.png 1375w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ITMaster-PIc-1-300x202.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ITMaster-PIc-1-1024x688.png 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ITMaster-PIc-1-768x516.png 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/ITMaster-PIc-1-1200x806.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> This impressive performance is packed into a form factor that uses a 360-degree hinge for the most versatile working experience yet. Clamshell, tablet, and tent form factors are supported by the HP ProBook x360 11, and are complemented by an 11.6-inch HD touch display. This offers crisp image quality and improved functionality over non-touch alternatives. Another valuable feature of the ProBook x360 11 is that it is designed to withstand significant punishment, being drop tested from up to 122cm, and can even survive being splashed with water and drinks. Most importantly, this HP laptop has been designed with hybrid learning in mind and is optimised to support attendance of remote classes using tools like Microsoft Teams. The specifications of the HP ProBook x360 11 are detailed below. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-581236" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Pic-2-ITMaster.png" alt="" width="640" height="480" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Pic-2-ITMaster.png 1378w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Pic-2-ITMaster-300x225.png 300w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Pic-2-ITMaster-1024x768.png 1024w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Pic-2-ITMaster-768x576.png 768w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2022/04/Pic-2-ITMaster-1200x900.png 1200w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: 909px) 67vw, (max-width: 984px) 61vw, (max-width: 1362px) 45vw, 600px" /> iTMaster is a South African ICT business that specialises in selling laptops like the HP ProBook x360 11, and offers various managed IT services. The company is dedicated to ensuring South Africans are equipped effectively to receive a valuable education. “We’ve assisted more than 4,000 schools in South Africa, many of which are rural schools, and what we have noticed in the pandemic is the gap between the digitally elite and the digitally deprived,” said iTMaster CEO Stanton Pillay. The company therefore offers turnkey mobile educational solutions that combine powerful desktop and touchscreen devices – like the HP ProBook x360 11 – with effective software. It also understands that these types of solutions often go underused because they are not supported, which is why iTMaster goes beyond simply implementing technology and supports schools by providing training to teachers and learners. Get here to learn more about the ITMaster Education Initiative. Click here to get in contact with ITMaster.